title: SC volleyball falls to Eagles
text: SC volleyball falls to Eagles 0 comments Offensive struggles plagued the Southwestern College volleyball team for the third-straight match Wednesday evening. The Builders fell in three sets (25-15, 25-13, 25-22) to the Eagles of Oklahoma Wesleyan University inside the Mueller Sports Center in Bartlesville, Okla. Southwestern (7-18, 3-10 KCAC) put down just 22 kills in the match, and failed to hit above .100 in either of the three sets, while Oklahoma Wesleyan (21-6, 10-4 KCAC) hit .250 or better in each set en route to the sweep. Brittaney Craddock led Southwestern's offensive efforts with seven kills, while Briley Ware and Abby Warnke added five kills each. Ware posted a team-best .300 attack percentage in the match.
